# LoLLMs Structured Content Generation

Use `generate_structured_content` to force the LLM to output valid JSON conforming to a specific structure.

```python
from lollms_client import LollmsClient

lc = LollmsClient()

schema = {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "name": {"type": "string"},
        "age": {"type": "integer"}
    },
    "required": ["name", "age"]
}

result = lc.generate_structured_content(
    prompt="Generate a random persona",
    schema=schema
)
print(result)
```
